    {
      "href": "/zdom/list/tourist-cinema/",
      "user": "zdom",
      "slug": "tourist-cinema",
      "title": "tourist cinema",
      "desc": "films that make you fantasize about spaces/places through travel without any real idea or representation of the identity of that country/city/place or peoples.\n\ninspiration is one thing and representation is another.\n---------------------------------------------------------------------\nthe transnational tourist gaze extends the concept of the \"tourist gaze\" originally developed by sociologist John Urry — to a global context, where media, film, and digital platforms shape how travelers perceive and desire destinations across national borders. \n\nit reflects how global audiences are influenced by visual and cultural representations in transnational cinema, advertising, and social media, leading to standardized or romanticized expectations of places and people which often marginalizes the country of origin, presenting it through a selective, external lens that prioritizes western or global consumer expectations over local realities. \n\nthis results in a distorted or romanticized representation—reducing complex cultures to stereotypes while silencing local voices and lived experiences.",
      "owner": "List by zdom",
      "tags": [
        "film-tourist",
        "tourist-cinema",
        "transnational-tourist-gaze",
        "film-theory",
        "travel"
      ]
    }
